title: A tribe out of time: how Chenchus have been caught between ancestral past and uncertain future in Andhra Pradesh
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': None, 'base': 'https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/feeder/default.rss', 'value': 'A tribe out of time: how Chenchus have been caught between ancestral past and uncertain future in Andhra Pradesh'}
summary: The Chenchus of Penukumadugu have lived in the dense Nallamala forests for centuries, their existence intertwined with the wilderness around them. However, their inability to keep up with the relentless pace of modernisation has led to dwindling work opportunities under the MGNREGA. Nellore Sravani writes how the Chenchus, caught between an ancestral past and an uncertain future, are grappling with isolation, poverty, and an erosion of their traditional way of life

title: Eturnagaram Wildlife Sanctuary destruction: A cataclysm in the woods
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': None, 'base': 'https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/feeder/default.rss', 'value': 'Eturnagaram Wildlife Sanctuary destruction: A cataclysm in the woods'}
summary: A catastrophic weather phenomenon flattened an estimated 50,000 trees over 332 hectares in Mulugu’s Eturnagaram Wildlife Sanctuary on August 31, devastating the landscape. As officials and environment experts scramble to find out why it happened and what needs to be done, P. Laxma Reddy visits the site to report on the intricacies of the rare incident, its impact on the villagers and the future of a forest intertwined with their lives

title: What is a fair fare?
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': None, 'base': 'https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/feeder/default.rss', 'value': 'What is a fair fare?'}
summary: Bengaluru has recently seen a surge in complaints to the traffic police against autorickshaw drivers, mainly regarding erratic fare demands. However, drivers say tell Darshan Devaiah B.P. that their earnings are not keeping pace with soaring inflation, regardless of whether they opt for metered rides or register with aggregators. The last fare revision in Bengaluru was three years ago, while the aggregator commissions remain steep
